WEBVTT

00:01:59.627 --> 00:02:04.197
Thus began the legend of Rome’s 
defiant gladiator.

00:02:04.197 --> 00:02:06.235
As news of the rebellion spread,

00:02:06.235 --> 00:02:09.005
its ranks swelled with escaped slaves,

00:02:09.005 --> 00:02:12.235
deserting soldiers, and hungry peasants.

00:02:12.235 --> 00:02:13.645
Many were untrained,

00:02:13.645 --> 00:02:16.865
but Spartacus’s clever tactics 
transformed them

00:02:16.865 --> 00:02:19.505
into an effective guerrilla force.

00:02:19.505 --> 00:02:22.599
A second Roman expedition led by praetor
Varinius,

00:02:22.599 --> 00:02:25.545
was ambushed while the officer bathed.

00:02:25.545 --> 00:02:27.735
To elude the remaining Roman forces,

00:02:27.735 --> 00:02:31.845
the rebels used their enemy’s corpses as
decoy guards,